/use></svg></a>Generalized (Truly) Dynamic Factor Models</h3>\n<p>Any dynamic factor model can be equivalently represented as a static factor model, where the polynomial lags operator is simply </p>\n<p>Estimation of the <em>generalized</em> factors is much more difficult.</p>\n<p>[<a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">@forni_generalized_2000 (Private)</a>] demonstrate that the dynamic principal components estimator, which is the </p>\n<h4 id=\"inferential-assumptions\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#inferential-assumptions\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Inferential Assumptions</h4>\n<h2 id=\"structural-breaks-in-dynamic-factor-models\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#structural-breaks-in-dynamic-factor-models\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Structural Breaks in Dynamic Factor Models</h2>\n<h2 id=\"state-of-the-art-approaches\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#state-of-the-art-approaches\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>State of the Art Approaches</h2>\n<h2 id=\"empirical-study\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#empirical-study\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Empirical Study</h2>\n<p>Do an empirical study showing </p>\n<h3 id=\"datasets\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#datasets\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Datasets</h3>\n<p>We consider 4 four different large empirical macroeconomic datasets.</p>\n<p>These are FRED-MD []</p>\n<h2 id=\"proposal\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#proposal\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Proposal</h2>\n<h2 id=\"anticipated-timeline\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#anticipated-timeline\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Anticipated Timeline</h2>\n<h2 id=\"requirements\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#requirements\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Requirements</h2>\n<h2 id=\"references\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#references\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>References</h2>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"children\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#children\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Children</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/3RtD305EvXc6EBxOMW4hK\">Confirmation Presentation</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.han_tests_2015","alias":"@han_tests_2015","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":120,"offset":727},"end":{"line":21,"column":135,"offset":742},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.han_tests_2015"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.baltagi_estimating_2021","alias":"@baltagi_estimating_2021","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":156,"offset":763},"end":{"line":21,"column":180,"offset":787},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.baltagi_estimating_2021"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1,"offset":2366},"end":{"line":50,"column":12,"offset":2377},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"t